We have seen it, women like Jill Biden — diligent, dedicated and ambitious — who have put in years of back breaking, soul crushing hard work only to have a sparsely accomplished man overlook, downplay and belittle their accomplishments simply because they are women.
In a classy response, Dr Jill Biden tweeted; “Together, we will build a world where the accomplishments of our daughters will be celebrated, rather than diminished.”
 However, I think it is time we began teaching our sons to be comfortable with highly accomplished women.
We need to let our boys know that a woman’s success does not translate to their personal failure and that it is perfectly okay to have a world in which both boys and girls succeed because there is enough success to go round.
